  "prompt": "Who invented the English alphabet?",
  "response": "The English alphabet is derived from the Latin alphabet, which itself evolved from earlier writing systems. The Latin alphabet was adapted from the Etruscan alphabet, which was influenced by the Greek alphabet. The Greek alphabet, in turn, descended from the Phoenician writing system. \n\nWhile no single individual \"invented\" the English alphabet, it was shaped over centuries through the adoption and adaptation of these earlier alphabets. The current 26-letter English alphabet was standardized in the 15th century, but its origins trace back to scripts developed thousands of years earlier.",
